<div id="review_1125240840" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1125240840" />
    <a title="Alondra Miller" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6130276-alondra-miller"><img alt="Alondra Miller" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641394385p2/6130276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1125240840?book_show_action=true">Dec 06, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alondra Miller" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alondra Miller" href="/user/show/6130276-alondra-miller">Alondra Miller</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6130276-alondra-miller?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6130276-alondra-miller?shelf=books-i-own">books-i-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6130276-alondra-miller?shelf=dystopian">dystopian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1125240840" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8956249585293375613">4 Stars<br/><br/>There is not a lot of action to this series. Just a sad commentary about human nature, to destroy the good in others. <br/><br/>This is the end of this series; and we have come full circle. We get answers, much needed. We also find peace in the end. <br/><br/>The stories can be a little long-winded and tedious at times with the details; but those details hold a lot of information. I loved Claire&apos;s journey to finding her son, and her son&apos;s journey to finding her. His was not nearly as painful; but just as ted</span>
  <span id="freeText8956249585293375613" style="display:none">4 Stars<br /><br />There is not a lot of action to this series. Just a sad commentary about human nature, to destroy the good in others. <br /><br />This is the end of this series; and we have come full circle. We get answers, much needed. We also find peace in the end. <br /><br />The stories can be a little long-winded and tedious at times with the details; but those details hold a lot of information. I loved Claire's journey to finding her son, and her son's journey to finding her. His was not nearly as painful; but just as tedious and daunting. <br /><br />Overall, I liked how things panned out, and I liked the ending. Neat, with a tidy bow on top.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8956249585293375613" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
